From daee547c435ac0a312ae0da29967dd0e9fd15117 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Fuchs <benjamin.fuchs@adorsys.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 12:19:05 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(BUG-12,BUG-13): architecture SSOT + SSRF URL validation

BUG-12: Architecture adrText/adrTitle now sourced from sessionState (SSOT),
not LLM-supplied toolArgs. Fixed variable scoping bug where adrText/adrTitle
were declared inside else-if block but referenced in outer logging block,
causing silent ReferenceError on string toolArgs. Added mismatch logging.

BUG-13: fetchUrlContent() now validates URLs via validateReviewUrl() before
fetch. Blocks non-HTTPS schemes, private/reserved IPv4 (127/8,10/8,172.16/12,
192.168/16,169.254/16,0.0.0.0), private IPv6 (::1,fc00::/7,fe80::/10), and
localhost. Changed redirect:'follow' to redirect:'error' (SSRF via redirects).
Uses existing COMMAND_BLOCKED reason code.

33 new tests (9 arch SSOT + 24 URL validation).
